    <note>Li(2) Juan [19767] In 1126, when Kaifeng was surrounded, the soldiers of the empire were summoned. At this time, Juan was Ezhou, Chongyang county magistrate and none of the soldiers of Ezhou had been assembled. He recruited city-dwellers, none of whom were trained in military matters, disbursed his family's money to buy oxen and wine to provide a banquet for them, led them East to Caizhou where he came upon the enemy and died in a bloody battle. CBD, 2, 855.</note>
